    "notes": "First WC in Africa. Spain's first title — Andrés Iniesta scored the winner in the 116th minute of a 1-0 a.e.t. win over Netherlands in the dirtiest WC final ever (14 yellow cards + Heitinga red). Defending champs Italy and runners-up France both crashed out in groups (France imploded after Anelka was sent home, players boycotted training). Suárez's deliberate handball denied Ghana victory over Uruguay in QF. Spain became first team ever to win a WC after losing their opening match. Müller won Golden Boot on assists tiebreak (also Best Young Player). Forlán Best Player. Casillas Best GK. Vuvuzelas dominated the soundscape. Octopus Paul correctly predicted 8 results.",
